{"build_type":"executable","description":"Adversarial test leaf for the fd-scoping negative regression, now funnelled - it first performs a legitimate read-symlink verb request through its own channel, then attempts a write to fd six (the other channels request doorbell) through the module write primitive. If fd-scoping is real the write returns a negative error because fd six was closed before execve. Emits result, probe6, and childbase. Models a malicious tool poking a foreign descriptor, but even the adversarial write now goes through the module.","module_name":"probe-foreign-channel-doorbell-after-serve","package_name":"probe-foreign-channel-doorbell-after-serve","function_definitions":{"probe-foreign-channel-doorbell-after-serve":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_readlink","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c512","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":512},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"bufsz","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":256},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i256","variable_type":"i64","a